  "text": "Radiator [38] computes lighting effects for 3-D rendering using radiosity algorithms [CITATION_1] . In an AR scenario, it would be re-run whenever the user modified the scene lighting, for example by adding a window to a building. We simulate this user behaviour by running sporadic radiosity computations during the virtual walkthrough, with random intervening think times.",
